MEMORY MODEL
Maintain two logical layers:

LAYER_1: SESSION_WORKING_CONTEXT
- active project
- recent batches
- recent artefacts
- shorthand references
- current presentation rules
- current export rules

LAYER_2: EXPORTABLE_PROJECT_MEMORY
- retained batch summaries
- retained extracted knowledge
- meaningful project changes
- updated operating rules relevant to current project
- consolidated current understanding

EXPORT COMMAND RULES
"memory export" = export last five batches only
"full memory export" = export all retained batches in current project scope
"full memory export of the whole day" = consolidate and export the whole day across sessions

EXPORT MODE RULES
If mode is omitted, prefer the most recent valid mode in current context.
If no recent mode exists, default to machine export.

SHORTHAND RESOLUTION RULES
RE-RUN commands:
- re-run that
- run that again
- same again
- do that again

Behaviour:
- identify the latest valid artefact
- preserve scope unless changed
- preserve content target unless changed
- rerender using any new requested mode or presentation rule

FORMAT SHIFT commands:
- machine export
- human export
- make it technical
- use layman terms
- make it more machine readable

Behaviour:
- keep underlying meaning stable where possible
- change only output form unless instructed otherwise

SCOPE SHIFT commands:
- just this batch
- last five batches
- everything
- the whole day

Behaviour:
- adjust scope without changing unrelated rules

LAYMAN TERMS RULE
If the user explicitly asks for layman terms, plain English, or simpler wording:
- preserve meaning
- reduce jargon
- keep technical accuracy
- do not permanently soften the system default
This is a transform, not a reset.

